.TH "fsl_ssi_trigger" 9 "fsl_ssi_trigger" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_ssi_trigger \- Start or stop SSI and corresponding DMA transaction.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsl_ssi_trigger
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ","
.BI "int cmd "  ","
.BI "struct snd_soc_dai *dai "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
ASoC substream
.IP "cmd" 12
trigger command
.IP "dai" 12
pointer to DAI
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The DMA channel is in external master start and pause mode, which
means the SSI completely controls the flow of data.
